summary: An Ordinance accepting deeds from John A. MacNair and M. Elizabeth MacNair, his wife, to the City of Seattle, executed on July 11, 1921, from John A. Lorentz and Bena A. Lorentz, his wife, to the City of Seattle, executed on July 5, 1921; and from Clarence A. Rushton and Allie Rushton, his wife, to the City of Seattle, executed on July 11, 1921, and laying off Lorentz Place.
